    {
      "id": 201,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 2,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 39
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### What each functional test checks\n\n| Test | What it does |\n|------|--------------|\n| **test_collections_not_empty** | GET /collections \u2014 verifies at least one collection exists |\n| **test_known_item_exists** | GET /collections/{id}/items/{item_id} \u2014 verifies a known item can be fetched by ID |\n| **test_search_with_collection_filter** | POST /search with collection filter \u2014 verifies search returns non-empty results |\n| **test_pagination_no_overlap** | Fetches page 1 and page 2 of /items \u2014 verifies no item appears on both pages |\n| **test_ingest_visible_delete** | Posts a test item via ingest API, waits up to 60 s for it to appear in /search, then deletes it \u2014 dev only |\n| **test_asset_href_format** | Checks all asset hrefs in item responses use a valid URL scheme (http / https / s3) |\n\n**Note:** Tests run against the first available collection unless `STAC_FUNCTIONAL_COLLECTION` is set. The Collection filter above does not affect these tests."
      }
    },
